00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.186
Hello Friends, 

00:00:01.186 --> 00:00:04.000
In this video today, we are going to talk health Insurance.  
 
 
 
 

00:00:04.000 --> 00:00:07.407
You all already have a basic understanding about health insurance 

00:00:07.407 --> 00:00:08.782
like what health insurance is about 

00:00:08.782 --> 00:00:12.939
but in this video we are going to discuss in detail the recommended health insuance product for you. 

00:00:12.939 --> 00:00:14.213
 
What all features does it have?

00:00:14.682 --> 00:00:18.746
Which all problems will be covered after some waiting period?

00:00:18.934 --> 00:00:24.248
 
What are the exclusions in the policy?
 

00:00:24.653 --> 00:00:31.968
 
More importantly, what all riders we should take out of the many offered by the company, not mandatory but good to have.

00:00:31.968 --> 00:00:34.718
 
So without wasting any time, lets get started.

00:00:49.723 --> 00:00:53.086
Before understanding health insurance and its features, 

00:00:53.086 --> 00:00:55.868
let us first understand the structure of how it acutally works

00:00:55.868 --> 00:01:00.000
Basically, there are three actors/participants in health insurance 

00:01:00.000 --> 00:01:04.376
1. Yourself (insured) - person buying the policy 

00:01:04.845 --> 00:01:07.939
2. Insurance company - Whose policy you are buying

00:01:08.093 --> 00:01:15.658
3. Hospital - from where treatment will be taken in case of any medical problem

00:01:15.658 --> 00:01:16.872
So in this case,

00:01:16.872 --> 00:01:18.872
 first condition 

00:01:18.872 --> 00:01:22.748
for claim settlment through health insurance is

00:01:22.748 --> 00:01:30.641
THAT Hospitalization tenure has to be of minimum 24 yrs

00:01:30.641 --> 00:01:32.641
otherwise insurance company will not settle the claim

00:01:32.641 --> 00:01:36.000
There is one exception to this rule which we will discuss in some time

00:01:36.000 --> 00:01:39.250
but for the time being just understand that minimum hospitalization of 24 hr is required 

00:01:39.250 --> 00:01:42.938
otherwise insurance company will not settle the claim

00:01:42.938 --> 00:01:48.000
Now, insurance company can settle the claim in two ways

00:01:48.000 --> 00:01:50.598
1. Cashless Claim Settlement

00:01:51.192 --> 00:01:55.130
2. Reimbursement of Claim

00:01:55.130 --> 00:02:01.788
Cashless means if you are getting your treatment from a hospital

00:02:01.788 --> 00:02:04.726
which is a part of insurance company's panel list

00:02:04.726 --> 00:02:06.000
then  

00:02:06.000 --> 00:02:11.220
You won't have to pay as insurance company will pay directly to hospital

00:02:11.220 --> 00:02:15.940
means, no money is getting debited from your account towards hospitalization expense (except for unclaimed amount)

00:02:15.940 --> 00:02:19.190
and you get treatment in pure cashless manner

00:02:19.190 --> 00:02:25.285
if you take treatment from a hospital which is not a part of insurance company's penal list

00:02:25.285 --> 00:02:31.068
then the process is that Firstly, you pay to the hospital  for your treatment

00:02:31.068 --> 00:02:35.705
then, you submit the bills to insurance company and file claim for reimbursement

00:02:35.705 --> 00:02:38.331
Insurance company will verify your claim

00:02:38.331 --> 00:02:44.083
and if verified, then reimbursement amount will be transferred to your account

00:02:44.083 --> 00:02:47.267
See friends, In both the case

00:02:47.267 --> 00:02:53.050
be it cashless or reimbursement claim settlement

00:02:53.050 --> 00:02:55.738
your are eligible for 100% settlement

00:02:55.738 --> 00:02:59.098
So it means this policy do not have co - payment

00:02:59.098 --> 00:03:04.787
It is not like if bill amounts to 2 lac then company will pay only 1.8 lac 

00:03:04.974 --> 00:03:13.039
Company will pay the entire 2 lac (except for uncovered amount) provided your diagnosis is covered under the policy

00:03:13.039 --> 00:03:16.977
So the first point of this slide says the same thing

00:03:16.977 --> 00:03:21.710
that if you are getting your hospitalization from one of the penal list hospital 

00:03:21.867 --> 00:03:24.000
then you are eligible for cashless treatment

00:03:24.000 --> 00:03:29.846
And there are more than 7000 hospitals available PAN India for this facility

00:03:29.846 --> 00:03:39.730
AYUSH Treatment - Ayurvedic, Unani, Satvic or Homopathic 

00:03:39.730 --> 00:03:42.293
You can take any treatment but condition remains the same 

00:03:42.293 --> 00:03:45.075
Minimum hospitalization of 24 hrs is mandatory for claim

00:03:45.075 --> 00:03:49.850
and treatment hospital should be a registered hospital

00:03:49.850 --> 00:03:53.664
Should not be a street clinic with hardly any hospital beds

00:03:53.664 --> 00:04:00.605
There is a certain criteria that make local clinic - a eligible hospital

00:04:00.824 --> 00:04:04.950
For ex the number of beds among other things

00:04:05.125 --> 00:04:09.357
AYUSH treatment is covered upto sum insured. No CAPPING

00:04:09.357 --> 00:04:19.557
For 10 lac policy, claim upto 10 lacs can be taken under AYUSH

00:04:19.776 --> 00:04:22.057
GUARANTEED No Claim Bonus

00:04:22.057 --> 00:04:25.152
One of the best benefit of this policy

00:04:25.152 --> 00:04:27.875
If Ipurchase a policy for 10 lacs sum insured

00:04:27.875 --> 00:04:30.781
then company says if you dont take any claim 

00:04:30.781 --> 00:04:37.814
then company will increase your base policy sum insured by 20%

00:04:37.814 --> 00:04:46.754
Means 10 lac policy will increase to 12 lacs after 1st year of no claim

00:04:46.754 --> 00:04:49.577
after that

00:04:51.578 --> 00:05:05.458
In second year if I get a claim then what other companies usually does is 

00:05:05.458 --> 00:05:09.271
they roll back the added 2 lac sum insured in event of claim making sum insured available in third year back to 10 lacs

00:05:09.271 --> 00:05:13.022
But this policy the addition wont be substracted

00:05:13.022 --> 00:05:16.591
10 lac to 12 lacs in case of no claim in first year, 

00:05:16.591 --> 00:05:18.216
claim in 2nd year

00:05:18.216 --> 00:05:20.216
This wont be reduced to 10 lac but will remain 12 lacs

00:05:20.216 --> 00:05:23.217
Means in case of claim, there will be no addition and no substraction

00:05:23.217 --> 00:05:26.061
Means your policy will remain for 12 lacs

00:05:28.731 --> 00:05:32.433
If again there is no claim in third year, then this sum insured will increase again by 20% to 14 lacs

00:05:32.433 --> 00:05:38.716
and it will continue in this manner till it reaches 20 lacs

00:05:38.935 --> 00:05:48.947
Meaning my 10 lac policy will underwent 5 upgrades of 20% each for every no claim year till policy reaches 20 lacs

00:05:48.947 --> 00:06:02.139
after which it will stop and stay at 20 lacs

00:06:02.139 --> 00:06:08.971
That was all about Guaranteed No claim bonus

00:06:08.971 --> 00:06:12.974
SUM INSURED RESTORE

00:06:12.974 --> 00:06:15.189
Lets understand this with the help of example.

00:06:15.189 --> 00:06:19.440
There is a person A who has bought this policy for 10 lacs

00:06:19.440 --> 00:06:24.000
Now Mr. A underwent a heart problem for which 8 lac claim came

00:06:24.000 --> 00:06:31.028
So obviously, out of 10 lac policy, 8 lac paid by company in claim -&gt; Remaining cover left is 2 lacs

00:06:33.904 --> 00:06:42.000
The very same year, if Mr A underwent another Heart problem and again 2nd claim of 8 lac came

00:06:42.000 --> 00:06:46.927
then company says we will restore your policy sum insured back to original

00:06:46.927 --> 00:07:01.811
meaning that leftover cover of 2 lac will be increased back to 10 lac for settling the claim of 8 lacs in full again

00:07:01.811 --> 00:07:07.094
So SuM INSureD REstoration essentially means that 

00:07:07.094 --> 00:07:13.493
your sum insured of base policy will be reinstated once it is exhausted

00:07:13.493 --> 00:07:15.940
Lets take another example for better understanding

00:07:15.940 --> 00:07:21.938
Two members are covered in the same policy - A and B (Sum insured 10 lacs)

00:07:21.938 --> 00:07:23.938
Mr. A takes claim for 3 lacs -&gt; Leftover claim -&gt; 7 lacs

00:07:23.938 --> 00:07:33.190
Mr. B takes claim for 4 lacs -&gt; leftover claim -&gt; 3 lacs

00:07:33.440 --> 00:07:38.237
Now Mr. A again underwent some problem (be it same or different it doesn't matter)

00:07:38.237 --> 00:07:42.000
as this restoration works for same person same illness as well

00:07:42.000 --> 00:07:49.715
So if again Mr. A needs 8 lac for treatment then company will refill this 3 lacs back to 10 lacs and settle the claim in full

00:07:51.810 --> 00:07:55.461
Important point to be noted here is that

00:07:55.461 --> 00:07:58.023
Once your base policy sum insured (10 lacs) is completely exhaused

00:07:58.023 --> 00:08:01.283
after that company will reinstate your sum insured only once and settle claim

00:08:01.283 --> 00:08:06.128
As in here 3 lac was increased to 10 lacs and of which they will settle 8 lac claim

00:08:06.128 --> 00:08:09.066
but there will be nothing left after this for further claim settlement

00:08:09.066 --> 00:08:11.066
irrespective of whether Mr. A is claiming or Mr. B is claiming

00:08:11.066 --> 00:08:17.408
Nothing is available now as your have taken claim for more money than your base policy

00:08:17.408 --> 00:08:21.812
Now there can be a confusion here wrt to Guaranteed no claim bonus

00:08:21.812 --> 00:08:23.812
